\r\n\r\n### Probable cause\r\nAfter some investigation on my side, this behaviour seems to be caused by `Phoenix.Endpoint.CowboyHandler.child_spec/3` and the private function `Phoenix.Endpoint.CowboyHandler.default_for/1`.\r\nThe `default_for/1` function is called by `child_spec/3` in order to resolve the `handler` module for the connection. But `default_for/1` does return `nil` for every passed in argument except the built in transports `LongPoll` and `WebSocket` which causes the handler to be `nil` for any custom transport.\r\nAs a result, the cowboy dispatches list does not contain dispatch items for custom transports which  does explain the 404s when a custom transport is used (to the best of my knowledge).\r\nFor the relevant code see [cowboy_handler.ex lines 83 to 113](https://github.com/phoenixframework/phoenix/blob/master/lib/phoenix/endpoint/cowboy_handler.ex#L83-L113)\r\nThe same issue seems to be present within the [cowboy2_handler.ex module](https://github.com/phoenixframework/phoenix/blob/master/lib/phoenix/endpoint/cowboy2_handler.ex#L80-L118).\r\n","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/phoenixframework/phoenix/issues/2869","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/phoenixframework/phoenix","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/phoenixframework/phoenix/issues/2869/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/phoenixframework/phoenix/issues/2869/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/phoenixframework/phoenix/issues/2869/events","html_url":"https://github.com/phoenixframework/phoenix/issues/2869","id":318849115,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMTg4NDkxMTU=","number":2869,"title":"Prepare for deprecation of System.stacktrace/0","user":{"login":"michalmuskala","id":477062,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3NzA2Mg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/477062?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/michalmuskala","html_url":"https://github.com/michalmuskala","followers_url":"https://api.githu